6FM8eQ==\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering class resource loading**\\n\\nI’m thinking about whether class resource loading requires the interface resource in the temp directory as well. I see that AntClassLoader can load interfaces from the parent class if \\\"includeAntRuntime\\\" is set to true in the system classpath. But if the parent is loaded first, then what happens? It seems like the project’s createClassLoader might be using AntClassLoader and the paths could include the parent class, though I’m still uncertain.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Analyzing test patterns**\\n\\nI'm noticing a pattern in the tests that makes me think I need to directly use getRemoteInterface without any error handling. It seems like I might be dealing with an ordinary class literal instead of a dynamic one. I'm also wondering if the dynamic report will require a loadClass call, based on the isValidRmiRemote line. But wait—it seems the source scanner must call the mapper to identify the target. That feels like a crucial insight, so I'm glad I caught it!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_i20XiEzQ0IVyPvvKEgm8oeUb|fc_04a8b1b9b1240b5b0169f56de69b58819fa503256372dc92fa", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/ant/ant/1.6/src/test/java/ant/ant/RmicTest.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage ant.ant;\n\nimport java.io.IOException;\nimport java.io.InputStream;\nimport java.nio.file.FileTime;\nimport java.nio.file.Files;\nimport java.nio.file.Path;\nimport java.rmi.Remote;\n\nimport org.apache.tools.ant.Project;\nimport org.apache.tools.ant.taskdefs.Rmic;\nimport org.graalvm.internal.tck.NativeImageSupport;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.io.TempDir;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\npublic class RmicTest {\n    @TempDir\n    Path temporaryDirectory;\n\n    @Test\n    void verifyModeLoadsCandidateClassBeforeSkippingUpToDateStub() throws IOException {\n        copyClassToTemporaryClasspath(RmicRemoteContract.class);\n        copyClassToTemporaryClasspath(RmicRemoteService.class);\n        createUpToDateStubFor(RmicRemoteService.class);\n\n        Rmic rmic = newRmic();\n        rmic.setBase(temporaryDirectory.toFile());\n        rmic.setClassname(RmicRemoteService.class.getName());\n        rmic.setStubVersion(\"1.2\");\n        rmic.setVerify(true);\n\n        try {\n            rmic.execute();\n        } catch (Error error) {\n            if (!NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError(error)) {\n                throw error;\n            }\n        }\n\n        assertThat(rmic.getLoader()).isNotNull();\n        assertThat(rmic.getCompileList()).isEmpty();\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void remoteInterfaceResolutionRecognizesDirectRemoteInterface() {\n        Rmic rmic = newRmic();\n\n        Class<?> remoteInterface = rmic.getRemoteInterface(RmicRemoteService.class);\n\n        assertThat(remoteInterface).isSameAs(RmicRemoteContract.class);\n    }\n\n    private Rmic newRmic() {\n        Project project = new Project();\n        project.init();\n\n        Rmic rmic = new Rmic();\n        rmic.setProject(project);\n        rmic.setTaskName(\"rmic\");\n        return rmic;\n    }\n\n    private void copyClassToTemporaryClasspath(Class<?> type) throws IOException {\n        String classResourceName = type.getName().replace('.', '/') + \".class\";\n        Path classFile = temporaryDirectory.resolve(classResourceName);\n        Files.createDirectories(classFile.getParent());\n\n        try (InputStream inputStream = RmicTest.class.getClassLoader()\n                .getResourceAsStream(classResourceName)) {\n            assertThat(inputStream).isNotNull();\n            Files.copy(inputStream, classFile);\n        }\n    }\n\n    private void createUpToDateStubFor(Class<?> type) throws IOException {\n        String stubResourceName = type.getName().replace('.', '/') + \"_Stub.class\";\n        Path stubFile = temporaryDirectory.resolve(stubResourceName);\n        Files.createDirectories(stubFile.getParent());\n        Files.write(stubFile, new byte[] {0});\n        Files.setLastModifiedTime(\n                stubFile,\n                FileTime.fromMillis(System.currentTimeMillis() + 60_000L));\n    }\n}\n\ninterface RmicRemoteContract extends Remote {\n}\n\nclass RmicRemoteService implements RmicRemoteContract {\n}\n"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1930, "output": 2499, "cacheRead": 27648, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 32077, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777692111292, "responseId": "resp_04a8b1b9b1240b5b0169f56dcfc270819fadecde6a8f112622"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_i20XiEzQ0IVyPvvKEgm8oeUb|fc_04a8b1b9b1240b5b0169f56de69b58819fa503256372dc92fa", "toolName": "write", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Successfully wrote 3148 bytes to tests/src/ant/ant/1.6/src/test/java/ant/ant/RmicTest.java"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1777692139036}]}
